{
  "stem": "1965.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I think that is where lies our strength-- to help each other, to stand by each other, to survive together, into the philosophy we are raised in.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And when we divide too much, then the tree and its branches start to fall off.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So to always do for each other gives strength to the root of the tree.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I came to Antwerp, I was nine years old.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the following year, I remember very well, my parents gave me for my tenth birthday a roll of pink toilet paper-- that was a big deal-- and a blue plastic belt.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was a big deal.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now the house we lived in was a concierge house for a synagogue.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It had, on the street level, one door with stoops and a door that opened up with a ding-a-ling-ling bell.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That led to our hallway to go upstairs to our quarters.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Next to that was two very large doors.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When you opened them-- you-- people who used to go to the synagogue before the war would enter this.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they would walk all the way down in the back to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The synagogue, unfortunately, was bombed during the war, so it was not in use after the war.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And my brother Jackie found the most gorgeous menorah there, which was re-donated to the actual owners.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the two boys and myself, we used to play in that synagogue.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That was our playground, that synagogue.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was very lovely, very sweet, very nice.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And right next to it was an asphalt place with chickens crawling.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And next to that were a couple houses.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And next to that was an army barracks with kazerne and so forth.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And every morning after the war I woke up with a bugle sound.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
